The first Day6 song I heard. I heard it in a KVille new song playlist back in late 2018 when I was getting into Kpop. One of the more interesting songs I heard at the time, with strong 80s theme in the song and the MV. It was my best decision to dive into more of their music!
This is the perfect concert song. Full of energy and great to single along to. Happy Day6 is so much fun.
This was a great follow up to Time of Our Life and another great concert song. I love the jazzy trill piano in the chorus. I also love the colour fade in effects in the MV.
The Lockdown song. Sad that this was their last song before a year long hiatus. But it is so good.

This should be surprising no one. Day6 are my favourite group when it comes to music alone. I genuinely have dozens of plays for every one of these songs, some of them over 100. They are close to being my most listened to group. It's sad that it looks like things are stopping for the group, with enlistments coming up, and one of my biggest regrest will be not making it to see them in Jan 2020 as it looks like I'll never be able to see them live now. RIP. However, we still have a 5 member comeback in April coming up that I am really looking forward to, so hoping to go out with a bang!
